&nbsp;
In front of the judges of the Capital's Examination Court, the leaders of the State Police Operational Service were heard: the director responsible, Vincenzo Nicolì and the manager Alessandro Gallo.&nbsp; The photos of the colonel> Uhsam Helmi, in sunglasses, blue jacket and white shirt, were shown in the courtroom of Rome.> They were taken when the Egyptian officer now under trial > participated on 10 February 2016 at the nickname obtained by Italian investigators in the place where Regeni's body was found.
&nbsp;
"The one with sunglasses is Colonel Helmi, he was present very often", confirmed Colonel of the Ros of the Carabinieri Loreto Biscardi, > who then explained: "We have never been provided with any footage, not even metro cameras. The indications from the local detective team were that of a plot against Egypt or even a terrorist action to attribute to the Muslim Brotherhood. Everything to complicate relations with Italy".
&nbsp;
Biscardi also recalled that "we came from a positive experience of exchanges with the Egyptian police, we were able to interrupt a few years before a traffic of migrants and the expectations on departure were to clarify the story. At the beginning - he continued - there was an apparent collaboration, they allowed us to attend the assumptions of testimonies but we were looking for objective feedback. From the outset the Egyptian authorities were informed that what had emerged from the autopsy carried out in Italy was not compatible with their investigative assumptions as the road accident."

